surveyResponses.text: How often did you hold multiple beliefs at a time (e.g., believing simultaneously that there are areas along the hillslope transect where data is needed, AND that there are potential discrepancies between measurements and the given hypothesis that needs to be further investigated)?
When you held multiple beliefs, how did you resolve them?
How satisfied were you with the suggested locations provided by the robot?
The robot’s suggestion was useful when I wanted to increase spatial coverage.
The robot’s suggestion was useful when I wanted to increase moisture-range coverage.
The robot’s suggestion was useful when I wanted to look into a potential discrepancy between measurements and the given hypothesis.
The robot’s suggestion was useful when I wanted to further verify that the measurements supported the given hypothesis.
The robot’s suggestions were not useful.
If you were to use this robot for data collection in real life, what changes or improvements would you make in how the robot interacts with you to suggest locations?
surveyResponses.value: I wouldn't make any drastic changes.  In a few particular instances, the robot continually suggested a location at the ridge of the slope where I believed there was already sufficient data.  Just a little curious about this.
